This subject gives an overview of the physical education in normal and special school. The topic about the children in special school centers mainly to the different levels of mental disabilities and how to find appropiate physical acitivity for these pupils. The topics of children with special needs in normal school give an overview how to adopt physical education activites to these kind of children.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give theoretical background and practical skills about the opportunities to develop people with special needs through physical exercises.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - knows different curriculums and physical education curriculums in different levels, its context and study results
- knows different forms of physical activities and exercises and the possibilites to adopt them accordingly to the special need
- analyses physical education lesson for the children with special needs, intensivity of the lesson and activities, choice of the exercises, teaching methods
